      problem:'A cross-seam delivery that goes straight and skids through the batter is a valuable surprise variation — but most bowlers have never practised it.',
      whyItMatters:'The cross-seam bouncer and cross-seam full ball both skid through at unexpected pace — surprising batters who set for swing or seam.',
      baseline:'Bowl 10 cross-seam deliveries; partner notes pace and low bounce vs. normal deliveries.',
      measurement:'Cross-seam effect: skid/pace + low bounce / same as normal',
