      steps:["Start in a relaxed crouch slightly wider than shoulder width, weight on the balls of the feet","As the bowler reaches release, take a small \"triangle\" half-step to set behind off stump","Track the ball out of the hand, not the pitch — adjust feet to the length, not the bounce","Stay tall enough through the take to move late if it turns more than expected","Reset to the base position before every delivery — never carry momentum into the next ball"],
      keyFocus:'Start in a relaxed crouch slightly wider than shoulder width, weight on the balls of the feet', commonError:'Rushing the fundamentals before they are grooved — speed and pressure should always be added last, never first',
